metadata.name: Hour
metadata.description: noun - a) a period of time equal to a twenty-fourth part of a day and night and divided into 60 minutes. b) a time of day specified as an exact number of hours from midnight or midday. c) a fixed period of time for an activity, such as work, use of a building, etc. d) (in the Western (Latin) Church) a short service of psalms and prayers to be said at a particular time of day, especially in religious communities. e) 15Â° of longitude or right ascension (one twenty-fourth part of a circle).
